  <section class="sec">
    <p class="sl">Local knowledge</p>
    <h2>Rowville — Knox Plateau 1970s & 1980s Estates, Dandenong Ranges Cold, Brick Fireplace Belt</h2>
    <div class="local-box"><p>Rowville is an established outer south-eastern suburb on the Knox plateau, developed primarily through the 1970s and 1980s as Melbourne's south-eastern suburban expansion pushed up onto the higher ground toward the Dandenong Ranges. The suburb's housing stock is dominated by brick veneer homes from this era — substantial four and five bedroom family homes where a single brick fireplace in the main living room was standard, and many of which were subsequently fitted with slow combustion heaters as owners upgraded the heating system over the years. These original brick chimneys are now forty to fifty years old and many have been in continuous use since the homes were built without a professional clean. Rowville's position on the Knox plateau creates a genuine winter cold pattern: the elevated ground above the Dandenong foothills is exposed to cold air draining off the ranges through still winter nights, and the suburb can be noticeably colder than suburban areas to the west. For many Rowville households the fireplace or slow combustion heater is the primary winter heating system, running through the full season. Annual cleaning is both a safety and performance necessity. We service Rowville and the surrounding Knox suburbs regularly.</p></div>
